<emphasis bold="true" box="[754,877,1261,1284]" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Metatibiae</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[892,956,1261,1284]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1827,1849]" captionTargetBox="[201,1368,320,1789]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[192,1395,311,1806]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 4. Pelecium igneus Orsetti &amp; Lopes-Andrade sp. nov., male holotype. 1, 3 dorsal view 2, 4 ventral view. 3. Head, arrowhead points to excavations of frontal fovea 4. Detail of labial and maxillary palpomeres. Scale bars: 5 mm (1 − 2); 1 mm (3 − 4)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261701/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
